A vintage-style illustration of an enormous antique wooden filing cabinet with hundreds of brass-handled drawers, some pulled open revealing glowing envelopes transforming into streams of golden data flowing upward. The cabinet sits in a cozy Victorian study with warm amber lighting from oil lamps. Scattered around the base are old leather-bound ledgers, brass compasses, and clockwork gears. The data streams converge into a floating crystalline sphere above the cabinet, where the envelopes reorganize themselves into an elegant honeycomb pattern. Dust motes catch the light, and ivy creeps through a nearby window. The color palette emphasizes rich browns, burnished gold, deep burgundy, and touches of electric blue where the digital transformation occurs. Rendered in detailed vintage scientific illustration style with cross-hatching and aged paper texture.
